{
  "texts": [
    "Equally, generative AI is being used as a contributor to an existing approach; it is essentially providing an advisory/ organizational add-on rather than being the complete solution-so Challenge 2 is satisfactorily dealt with.",
    "Challenges 3 and 4 are less clearly addressed by LLM application, but in the examples indicated there was a lower level of concern about privacy and data sharing.",
    "This is less likely to be the case in the future.",
    "LLM tools rely generally on the user being willing to \"share\" information passed to the LLM and the model itself is open to security challenges.",
    "The evolution of newer forms of LLMs-for example, so called private LLMs-run locally using a corporation's viii Foreword own data-present a prospect of more secure generative AI options for industry [8,9].Although AI appears to be a popular technology it is worth noting that the generative AI applications we are seeing are relatively simple, predominantly of the nature of providing advisory information and information organization capabilities."
  ]
}